<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D5EFFB9FF4DF993FCD5F891" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="207B96733D5EFFB9FF4DF993FCD5F891" blockId="45.[151,1437,1518,2013]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D5EFFB9FF4DF993FEA9F9E2" bold="true" box="[199,322,1626,1652]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D5EFFB9FE3FF992FDA9F9E2" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[437,578,1627,1652]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sutu" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D5EFFB9FE3FF992FDA9F9E2" box="[437,578,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Patrera sutu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D5EFFB9FDC3F992FD62F9E3" bold="true" box="[585,649,1627,1653]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0983F71A3D5EFFB9FDC3F992FD62F9E3" box="[585,649,1627,1653]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D5EFFB9FCE2F992FB30F9E3" authority="Duperre &amp; Tapia, 2016" authorityName="Duperre &amp; Tapia" authorityYear="2016" box="[872,1243,1627,1653]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philipi">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D5EFFB9FCE2F992FC26F9E3" box="[872,973,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">P. philipi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="4455EB823D5EFFB9FC5FF992FB30F9E3" author="Duperre, N. &amp; Tapia, E." box="[981,1243,1627,1653]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref40935" refString="Duperre, N. &amp; Tapia, E. (2016) Overview of the Anyphaenids (Araneae, Anyphaeninae, Anyphaenidae) spider fauna from the Choco forest of Ecuador, with the description of thirteen new species. European Journal of Taxonomy, 255, 1 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2016.255" type="journal article" year="2016">Dupérré &amp; Tapia, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D5EFFB9FA99F992FE77F90F" authority="Duperre &amp; Tapia, 2016" authorityName="Duperre &amp; Tapia" authorityYear="2016" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hatunkiru">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D5EFFB9FA99F992FA77F9E3" box="[1299,1436,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">P. hatunkiru</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="4455EB823D5EFFB9FF1DF9B6FE77F90F" author="Duperre, N. &amp; Tapia, E." box="[151,412,1663,1689]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref40935" refString="Duperre, N. &amp; Tapia, E. (2016) Overview of the Anyphaenids (Araneae, Anyphaeninae, Anyphaenidae) spider fauna from the Choco forest of Ecuador, with the description of thirteen new species. European Journal of Taxonomy, 255, 1 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2016.255" type="journal article" year="2016">Dupérré &amp; Tapia, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by having a large, strong ventral tegular process (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D5EFFB9FC45F9B6FBDFF90D" box="[975,1076,1663,1691]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1406,1430]" captionTargetBox="[159,1434,182,1382]" captionTargetId="figure-18@43.[151,1436,181,1382]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 23A–E. Patrera sutu n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10601): A habitus, dorsal view; B chelicerae, ventral view (Arrow: indicates projection of the chelicerae); C palp, ventral view (Arrow: indicating the left palp ventral view); D palp, retroventral view; E palp, ventral view. Abbreviations: E, embolus; Cvp, cheliceral ventral projection; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; SD, spermatic ducts; ST, subtegulum; T, tegulum; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B: 1mm; C: 0.2mm; D–E: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468435" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468435/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 23C</figureCitation>
̅E; 
<bibRefCitation id="4455EB823D5EFFB9FBEBF9B6FA83F90F" author="Duperre, N. &amp; Tapia, E." box="[1121,1384,1663,1689]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref40935" refString="Duperre, N. &amp; Tapia, E. (2016) Overview of the Anyphaenids (Araneae, Anyphaeninae, Anyphaenidae) spider fauna from the Choco forest of Ecuador, with the description of thirteen new species. European Journal of Taxonomy, 255, 1 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2016.255" type="journal article" year="2016">Dupérré &amp; Tapia, 2016</bibRefCitation>
: figs 41, 55), but can be diagnosed by the ventral tegular process apically bifid (entire in 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D5EFFB9FBC5F96AFB32F92B" authorityName="Duperre &amp; Tapia" authorityYear="2016" box="[1103,1241,1699,1725]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hatunkiru">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D5EFFB9FBC5F96AFB32F92B" box="[1103,1241,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">P. hatunkiru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and retrolateral tibial apophysis with the ventral branch apically sharp and longer than dorsal branch (the ventral branch is wider and adjacent to the dorsal one in 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D5EFFB9FD82F922FD7AF893" authorityName="Duperre &amp; Tapia" authorityYear="2016" box="[520,657,1771,1797]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hatunkiru">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D5EFFB9FD82F922FD7AF893" box="[520,657,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">P. hatunkiru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D5EFFB9FD20F922FCE4F891" box="[682,783,1771,1799]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1406,1430]" captionTargetBox="[159,1434,182,1382]" captionTargetId="figure-18@43.[151,1436,181,1382]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 23A–E. Patrera sutu n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10601): A habitus, dorsal view; B chelicerae, ventral view (Arrow: indicates projection of the chelicerae); C palp, ventral view (Arrow: indicating the left palp ventral view); D palp, retroventral view; E palp, ventral view. Abbreviations: E, embolus; Cvp, cheliceral ventral projection; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; SD, spermatic ducts; ST, subtegulum; T, tegulum; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B: 1mm; C: 0.2mm; D–E: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468435" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468435/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 23C</figureCitation>
̅E).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D5EFFBAFF4DF8C7FC2DFDAB" lastPageId="46" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="description">
<paragraph id="207B96733D5EFFBAFF4DF8C7FEDFFE45" blockId="45.[151,1437,1518,2013]" lastBlockId="46.[151,1436,150,609]" lastPageId="46" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D5EFFB9FF4DF8C7FEB2F8BE" bold="true" box="[199,345,1806,1832]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D5EFFB9FEE9F8C6FE76F8BF" box="[355,413,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="FF7F28D13D5EFFB9FE25F8C6FDF7F8BF" box="[431,540,1807,1833]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Holotype</typeStatus>
, ICN-Ar-10601). Carapace yellow, darker on the cephalic region (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D5EFFB9FAAEF8C6FA7BF8BF" box="[1316,1424,1807,1833]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1406,1430]" captionTargetBox="[159,1434,182,1382]" captionTargetId="figure-18@43.[151,1436,181,1382]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 23A–E. Patrera sutu n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10601): A habitus, dorsal view; B chelicerae, ventral view (Arrow: indicates projection of the chelicerae); C palp, ventral view (Arrow: indicating the left palp ventral view); D palp, retroventral view; E palp, ventral view. Abbreviations: E, embolus; Cvp, cheliceral ventral projection; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; SD, spermatic ducts; ST, subtegulum; T, tegulum; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B: 1mm; C: 0.2mm; D–E: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468435" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468435/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 23A</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae dark brown. Labium and endites yellow. Legs pale yellow. Sternum yellowish. Abdomen dorsally grayish; ventrally yellow. Spinnerets yellow (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D5EFFB9FDE3F89EFD38F8E7" box="[617,723,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1406,1430]" captionTargetBox="[159,1434,182,1382]" captionTargetId="figure-18@43.[151,1436,181,1382]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 23A–E. Patrera sutu n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10601): A habitus, dorsal view; B chelicerae, ventral view (Arrow: indicates projection of the chelicerae); C palp, ventral view (Arrow: indicating the left palp ventral view); D palp, retroventral view; E palp, ventral view. Abbreviations: E, embolus; Cvp, cheliceral ventral projection; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; SD, spermatic ducts; ST, subtegulum; T, tegulum; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B: 1mm; C: 0.2mm; D–E: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468435" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468435/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 23A</figureCitation>
). Total length 5.83, carapace length 2.41, width 2.0, high 0.91. Clypeus height 0.11. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.08, ALE 0.19, PME 0.17, PLE 0.19; AME–AME 0.22, AME–ALE 0.3, PME–PME 0.46, PME–PLE 0.4, ALE–PLE 0.39. Chelicerae 1.44 long, four promarginal teeth, six retromarginal teeth, with a large retromarginal and fissidentate Cvp (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D5EFFB9FB9DF80AFB6BF84B" box="[1047,1152,1987,2013]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="47.[151,250,1825,1849]" captionTargetBox="[208,1374,181,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-18@47.[208,1379,181,1801]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURE 24A–D. Patrera chucurui n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10632):A habitus, dorsal view; C chelicerae dorsal view; D chelicerae ventral view; E left palp, retrolateral view; F palp, ventral view; G palp, retrolateral view. Female (ICN-Ar-9684): B habitus, dorsal view; H epigynum, ventral view; I epigynum, dorsal view. Abbreviations: A, atrium; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; ST, subtegulum; T, tegulum; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C–D: 1mm; E–G: 0.5mm; H–I: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468437" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468437/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 24B</figureCitation>
). Leg measurements: leg I—femur 3.6/ patella 0.98/ tibia 3.93/ metatarsus 3.64/ tarsus 1.88/ total 14.05; II—3.33/ 1.08/ 3.84/ 3.29/ 1.56/ 13.11; III—2.16/ 0.87/ 1.96/ 2.48/ 0.97/ 8.46; IV—3.01/ 1.0/ 2.67/ 3.39/ 1.28/ 11.37. Leg spination: I—tibia v2-2- 0, r1-2-1; II—tibia v2-2-0, metatarsus v2-2-0; III—tibia d1-0-1, v2-2-0, p1-0-1, r0-1-1, metatarsus v2-2-0, p1-2-2, r1-1-2; IV—tibia p1-0-1, r1-0-1, metatarsus v2-2-0, p1-2-2, r1-1-2. Abdomen: length 2.85, epigastric furrow 0.64 from tracheal spiracle, spiracle 1.07 from base of spinnerets. Palp: retrolateral tibial apophysis bifid, long, with the ventral branch longer than dorsal one; cymbium almost as long as tibia; subtegulum longer than wide; tegulum longer than wide, with a strong, large, apically bifid ventral tegular process; median apophysis short, laminar, curved and apically situated; embolus short, apically filiform, with narrow base and proximally inserted on the tegulum (
<figureCitation id="B8FF8AF63D5DFFBAFF2AFE7EFEEEFE45" box="[160,261,439,467]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1406,1430]" captionTargetBox="[159,1434,182,1382]" captionTargetId="figure-18@43.[151,1436,181,1382]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 23A–E. Patrera sutu n. sp. Male (ICN-Ar-10601): A habitus, dorsal view; B chelicerae, ventral view (Arrow: indicates projection of the chelicerae); C palp, ventral view (Arrow: indicating the left palp ventral view); D palp, retroventral view; E palp, ventral view. Abbreviations: E, embolus; Cvp, cheliceral ventral projection; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; SD, spermatic ducts; ST, subtegulum; T, tegulum; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A: 2mm; B: 1mm; C: 0.2mm; D–E: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468435" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468435/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 23C</figureCitation>
̅E).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="207B96733D5DFFBAFF4DFE12FE49FE63" blockId="46.[151,1436,150,609]" box="[199,418,475,501]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D5DFFBAFF4DFE12FEF5FE63" bold="true" box="[199,286,475,501]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="207B96733D5DFFBAFF4DFE36FC2DFDAB" blockId="46.[151,1436,150,609]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D5DFFBAFF4DFE36FE67FD8E" bold="true" box="[199,396,510,537]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Natural History.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="FF7F28D13D5DFFBAFE4FFE36FDCCFD8F" box="[453,551,511,537]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected manually, in a protected high mountain wet forest ecosystem, to a height of 1830 meters. This species is sympatric with 
<taxonomicName id="E7C4EDF03D5DFFBAFC8CFDEAFC6BFDAB" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira, 2021" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Villarreal &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2021" box="[774,896,547,573]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Patrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perafani" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="12B04A613D5DFFBAFC8CFDEAFC6BFDAB" box="[774,896,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">P. perafani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="12B04A613D5DFFBAFC0DFDEAFC2DFDAB" bold="true" box="[903,966,547,573]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0983F71A3D5DFFBAFC0DFDEAFC2DFDAB" box="[903,966,547,573]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="68DEC5F83D5DFFBAFF4DFD8FFC7DFDF7" box="[199,918,582,609]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="207B96733D5DFFBAFF4DFD8FFC7DFDF7" blockId="46.[151,1436,150,609]" box="[199,918,582,609]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
